    "description": "Kyowa Engineering Consultants Co., Ltd. provides construction consultancy services in Japan and internationally. It operates through the Construction Consulting Business, Information Processing Business, and Real Estate Rental and Management Business segments. The company offers structure design and maintenance services, such as survey, planning, and design of bridges, underground structures, water and sewage facilities, tunnels, utility tunnels, etc.; inspection and repair technologies; construction management. It also provides regional development and creation services, including urban development, surveys, planning, and design of roads, parks, green spaces, and land development; surveys, predictions, and countermeasures for the social and natural environment; landscape studies. In addition, the company offers disaster prevention and mitigation services for investigation, planning, and design of rivers, waterways, sluice gates, and related facilities; erosion control-related investigations and planning; geotechnical and hydrological investigations and analyses, as well as surveys of energy reserves, including solar, hydro, wind, and biomass, implementation planning and design, regional utilization plans, and consensus building support; architecture services, such as seismic diagnosis of buildings, seismic design, and improvement of the asset value of building facilities, as well as investigation and design of drinking water development projects, construction supervision and support for non-revenue water countermeasures, and support for renewable energy development; and promoting small-scale hydropower generation and supporting regional revitalization. Additionally, the company engages in real estate rental and management; information processing; personnel dispatch; sale of information processing equipment; and software development activities. It serves government agencies. The company was incorporated in 1961 and is headquartered in Shibuya, Japan."
